refactor(audio,design): absorb reviewer-trio findings on PR #8

Security (NaN/Infinity guard):
- audioBus init now checks `Number.isFinite(persistedVolume)` and
  applies `clamp01` before assigning. Without this a tampered
  localStorage `NaN` flows into `Howl.volume(NaN)` (silently dropped
  by the Web Audio spec — symptom is silent audio rather than a
  crash) and `Infinity` produces `RangeError` in some browsers. New
  test in volume-from-kv.browser.test.ts covers NaN, Infinity, and
  out-of-range positive values.

Code review (Howler global registry leak):
- `__resetBusForTest` now calls a new `bus.__teardown()` method that
  `unload()`s every Howl instead of just `stop()`-ing them. Without
  this, Howler retains the orphaned Howls in its global
  `Howler._howls` registry across tests; pending 'end' events from
  the orphans could fire fades on a global audio graph the test no
  longer owns. Counter + flag also reset.

Simplifier (file-level structure):
- ducking.ts deleted; `duckAmbient` + `restoreAmbient` inlined as
  module-scope functions in audioBus.ts. The two helpers are only
  called from within the bus and don't have a separate testable
  surface (ducking tests exercise them via `play()`/`stop()` on the
  bus, not directly), so the abstraction overhead exceeded content.
- _setup.ts: removed redundant `Howler.ctx.resume()` block in
  beforeEach. The bounded resume already runs inside `init()` via
  `getAudioBus()` — the setup version was racing against a context
  that may not exist yet.
- design/tokens.ts: added `motion.uiCloseMs` (140) and
  `motion.screenFadeMs` (200) tokens. design/motion.ts no longer
  hardcodes durations — every variant now sources from
  `tokens.motion.*`.

Docs:
- DESIGN.md: documented the duck-no-op-when-ambient-not-playing
  edge so PRQ-2 sim authors aren't surprised by stings firing
  before `startAmbient()`.

Tests: 184 node + 33 browser passing locally (was 32; added one
NaN/Infinity guard test).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
